metadata.description: Franz Schubert was an Austrian composer who lived at the beginning of the 19th century. Schubert's musical talent was discovered at a young age and his passion for composing overflowed. He showed his mastery especially in his lied songs and symphonies. Schubert is known for his melancholic and emotional compositions. Despite his short life, he is remembered as a genius who left many unforgettable works to the world of music.
metadata.name: Franz Schubert #1/3
